  "lastReviewFeedback": "coderabbitai: **Actionable comments posted: 6**\n\n<details>\n<summary>🤖 Prompt for all review comments with AI agents</summary>\n\n```\nVerify each finding against the current code and only fix it if needed.\n\nInline comments:\nIn `@packages/hx-library/src/components/hx-nav/hx-nav.styles.ts`:\n- Around line 4-239: Replace all hardcoded color, spacing, typography and timing\nliterals in this stylesheet with the project's design tokens: swap hex/color\nfallbacks in [part='nav'], [part='toggle'], .nav__link, .nav__link--active,\n.nav__submenu, :host([orientation='vertical']) rules, etc., to use --hx- color\ntokens (e.g. --hx-nav-bg, --hx-nav-color, --hx-nav-link-hover-bg,\n--hx-nav-link-active-bg, --hx-nav-submenu-bg, etc.), replace rem/fallbacks for\nfont-size, padding, gap and min-width with --hx- spacing/typography tokens (e.g.\n--hx-nav-padding, --hx-nav-item-padding, --hx-space-*, --hx-font-size-*), and\nreplace hardcoded durations (150ms, 200ms) in transition rules for .nav__link,\n.nav__chevron and [part='toggle'] with timing tokens like\n--hx-transition-duration-small/medium; update any other literals (border-radius,\nbox-shadow offsets) to corresponding --hx- tokens so every literal is\ntoken-driven.\n\nIn `@packages/hx-library/src/components/hx-nav/hx-nav.ts`:\n- Around line 126-131: The keydown handler _handleKeydown is selecting all\n'[part=\"link\"]' including hidden submenu links, so the incoming top-level index\nno longer matches itemsArr; change the query to only select top-level links\n(e.g., scope to immediate children of the nav item container or filter links\nwhose closest('[part=\"item\"]') is a top-level item and not inside a\nsubmenu/hidden container), then rebuild itemsArr from that filtered list so\ncurrent = itemsArr[index] matches the top-level index; apply the same scoping\nchange to the other keyboard-navigation selection logic referenced around the\nsecond occurrence (the code at the other handler using\nquerySelectorAll('[part=\"link\"]')).\n- Around line 216-224: The documen",
